sources, including the material survivals of daily life in town and country, and on the history of government, religion, ideas, painting, literature, and architecture. As B. S. Gregory has put it, everyday history is 'an endeavour that seeks to identify and integrate everything - all relevant material, social, political, and cultural data - that permits the fullest possible reconstruction of ordinary life experiences in all their varied complexity, as they are formed and transformed.'  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aScottish Studies. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh1 aBlaikie, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Stewart J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurie, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoyster, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFraser, W. Hamish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffiths, Trevor, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGriffiths, Trevor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnox, W. W. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcKinlay, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris, R. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorton, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, Mairi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatson, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhatley, Christopher A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press B